magpie.models.regression

Class MultiObjectiveRegression

  • java.lang.Object
    • magpie.models.BaseModel
      • magpie.models.regression.BaseRegression
        • magpie.models.regression.MultiObjectiveRegression
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable, AbstractRegressionModel, Citable, Commandable, Options, Printable, Savable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    MultiPropertyRegression

    public class MultiObjectiveRegression
extends BaseRegression
    Employs multiple models, each designed to predict a different property that composes the class variable. Class variable is defined by a MultiObjectiveEntryRanker.

    Usage: <ranker method> [<ranker options...>]
    ranker method: Multi-objective function ("?" for options)
    ranker options: Any options for the objective function

    Implemented Commands:

    submodel - Print type and status of model associated with each property

    <model> = submodel get <property> - Get a model for a certain property
    property: Name of property associated with model

    submodel set <property> $<model> - Set a model for a certain property
    property: Name of property associated with model
    model: Regression model to use

    submodel set generic $<model> - Set a model for any property without an associated model
    model: Regression model to use

    <output> = submodel get <property> - Get a model associated with a certain property
    property: Name of property associated with desired model

    See Also:
    Serialized Form
